Stay until the end, its so calming & I find it satisfying.🙏
.
Mediation comes in many forms for the senses. 

𝗪𝗵𝗶𝗰𝗵 𝘀𝘁𝘆𝗹𝗲 𝗼𝗳 𝗺𝗲𝗱𝗶𝘁𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻 𝘀𝘂𝗶𝘁𝘀 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗺𝗼𝘀𝘁? 👇
.
📽by @yukikawae 🌱
✒@anxiety_wellbeing 
.
Meditation is anything where you are able to be present with one thing and there are many different ways you can get a sense of meditation.
.
Regularly connecting with something that brings you into the present moment is a sign to your mind & body that you are safe & not in need of the stress response, anxiety.
.
Where as regularly connecting to things that cause stress, like fearful news, or constant distractions & info are signs of overwhelm.
.
Meditation
Here are some things that I connect with.

📚Reading takes me to a place in my mind I love the imagination 
🏖The beach sounds & visuals distract all other thoughts I am at peace
🕊Looking for and listening to nature connects me to life, I feel part of it.
🎵Music touches my heart strings, it can lift me high, can help me to connect to emotions inside to release them. I feel alive.
🌞Being in the sun and I start to drink it in, taking deep breaths. I feel energised.
⛈Thunder & rain connects me to our planet. I could listen for ages & wonder at the sights sounds.
.
There are many more visual, sounds, senses that give me that one focus and calms all others.
.
I saw this visual meditation video & thought you guys might enjoy.
.
𝗗𝗶𝗱 𝗶𝘁 𝗯𝗿𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝗰𝗮𝗹𝗺? 
.
For me I could watch this over & over i get calm from it. & it makes me want to try these actions, I think it would inspire calm.
.
Enjoy 🙏
.

.

.
Daily habits
Food choices
Thought Management
Morning rituals
Reconnecting to nature
etc.

All these will impact our thoughts & feelings.
Reduce fear
Reduce anxiety
Boost wellbeing & immunity.
Win Win Win!
.
👉Each weekend we will go live for a Q & A. After the live, we will be posting up what you need, to be prepared for the week. (things you may already have or are very affordable to get) So that you don't arrive at one day and think "I am not ready" & then decide you can't join in. 
.

.
👉You can follow myself & @almaformula we will be doing the challenge ourselves & documenting this in our stories to give you two different perspectives from the challenge as well as your own. 
.
👉There will be links given as we go, for ideas, downloadables etc. as part of the challenge. 
.
👉If you are thinking you can't do this, it may be too long?
.

Life sometimes happens, even myself, I may have a day when it's not possible to achieve that days activity, like too many urgent things may take over. .

.
👉We are in control of our behaviours & this will impact/influence on our though & feelings.
.

👍Join us on Monday the 19th of october. Both myself & Priyanka @almaformula have collaborated to bring you this challenge & we will both be taking part.
.
🤔We will be consciously working on what we are in control of : behaviours such as 
.
Daily habits
Food choices
Thought Management
Morning rituals
Reconnecting to nature
etc.

All these will impact our thoughts & feelings.
Reduce fear
Reduce anxiety
Boost wellbeing & immunity.
Win Win Win!
.
👉Each Saturday we will go live for a Q & A. After the live, we will be posting up what you need, to be prepared for the week. (things you may already have or are very affordable to get) So that you don't arrive at one day and think "I am not ready" & then decide you can't join in. 
.
👉Each evening between 9pm French time we will be posting up what to do for the following day.
So that you know what to expect, as some of the activities are designed to be, as you wake up.
.
👉You can follow myself & @almaformula we will be doing the challenge ourselves & documenting this in our stories to give you two different perspectives from the challenge as well as your own. 
.
👉There will be links given as we go, for ideas, downloadables etc. as part of the challenge. 
.
👉If you are thinking you can't do this, it may be too long?
.
👉HERE'S a Helpful perception
Life sometimes happens, even myself, I may have a day when it's not possible to achieve that days activity, like too many urgent things may take over. That's fine & not a reason to beat myself up or decide I've failed, feel bad & the choose to not take part the next day. No i'll take the day I need & will be ready the next day.
.
👉Also this is a challenge to be taken with interest & discovery of self. To become aware of what behaviours we choose that may influence our thoughts & feelings. Not to tell ourselves off, but to know where we can make the first step.
.
👉We are in control of our behaviours & this will impact/influence on our though & feelings.
.
👉Up next is the shopping list.
👉Sunday 9pm gmt +1 Monday's challenge Will be posted.
👉Monday websites & links to what you need.

node.text:
What if I told you that 𝗮𝗻𝘅𝗶𝗲𝘁𝘆 & panic was the door & not the wall? WHAT! How is it the door? Read on👇
.
🎨@justbelmont 
✒@anxiety_wellbeing 
.
😭When I went through my second panic attack, I believed from that moment that I had hit a wall, that I was stuck, no way out, afraid all the time, allllllll the time. I ended up panicking every 30 minutes. 
.
🤯I believed I would have to be like that forever.
.
👉Fast forward to now, what did I learn?
.
🌱That anxiety is a response to a problem
Panic was a response to the fear of experiencing high anxiety not knowing what it was.
.
🚪I thought anxiety & panic was the all but it was the door.
.
🚪The door to asking myself, what had happened to cause anxiety?
.
🚪What had really been happening was I had been telling myself I was ok. That my life was normal. That I had no choice.
.
🚪Leading up to the anxiety & panic i had actually been very anxious for a while thinking it was normal.
.
😔I had lots of worries 
😔Problems at work
😔An abusive relationship 
😔Past issues at home 
😔No leanrt solutions or a good example around me
😔I Wasn't looking after me or my needs 
😔Putting energy into people I had no control over 
😔Not grabbing control of the only thing I did have control over, me, my ideas, actions, words.
.
& so my body responded with
Survival mechanism
Anxiety 
Stress response.
.
🆘️Without realising it, anxiety was a sign to look at my life & make a change or stay stressed in my body & mind.
.
If you are going through anxiety & or panic, I hope you read this.
.
🌱Anxiety & panic is not the problem, its problematic (good god I remember & believing it was got me stuck for 6 months ) but its the sign for change. 
.
🚪It is the door out of what you have leanrt to do, years of fighting/defending, fleeing/avoiding/moving or not knowing what to do. Frozen/protecting. Passed on by others or by what you have perceived from the past events in your life.
.
✅The good news is all that can be changed, re leanrt, practiced with a hand.
.
#anxiety #anxietycoach 
.
#anxietyhelp #locusofcontrol #copingskills #perception #human #wellbeing #prevention #resilience #recovery #solutions #ideas #cbt #support #holistic

node.text:
Feeling low & not knowing 𝗵𝗼𝘄 𝘁𝗼 help yourself can cause you to freeze. The siutation becomes bigger than you think 💭you can handle & to much👇
.
🎨@mindspo
✒@anxiety_wellbeing 
.
👉having a few things that you can go-to can help with feelings of overwhelm.
.
Sadness is a response to something that's happened/happening. The clues are in that.
You could be low because a vitamin & mineral deficiency that is causing tiredness, then tired you feel you cannot cope, then sad & anxious.
Or overwhelmed with problems not knowing what to do, stressed & sad. Etc.
.
Also blocking the sadness can be a cause for anxiety & feeling lower. If you feel sad you have reason, you felt it. You perceive the situation to be sad, even if noone else does you may do, thats OK but not nice.
.
The feelings are valid & you must validate that you feel sad & allow them emotions to pass through you. 
.
E-motion. Energy in motion❤
.
Plus when we block sadness or think we are helpless & potentially stuck this can cause fear & panic because fear causes anxiety & panic. 
.
Its not easy & it makes sense, trying to work out how you feel, allowing it & then getting solution based is not easy especially if you have no prior experience or had someone to show you or guide you to do that. We learn from our peers & if they didn't work through things then you've not learnt either.
.
Not easy does not mean cannot be done, & there is one thing for sure you need to reach out. For advice, guidance, ideas, solutions & to allow yourself to do that. Many people get stuck because they believe its not possible & that they can't, are afraid of judgement, of feeling humiliated. My lovely, i am sorry you are going through that or that when you tried before it didn't seem to work but keep looking for it, keep open, learning, you are capable & enough ❤
.
You need
compassion & acceptance especially with yourself 
ideas, help, guidance, practice, to have people who inspire to look to for ideas, to talk, to aquire new skills and put them into practice.

There's nothing wrong with you, you need to learn how & have a hand to do it❤
.

There is 𝗻𝗼𝘁𝗵𝗶𝗻𝗴 wrong with being either or in-between. But you may need a little of your opposite 👇
.
🎨@theserenefactor 😍
✒@anxiety_wellbeing
.
🤔GUILT
1 of the main reasons some people feel they can't enjoy feeling introvert at times is a belief that it's wrong, that you are somehow weird for being yourself. Thinking 'what's wrong with me?'. These thoughts can bring feelings of fear & this can cause anxiety, your stress response.
.
🦄MYTH
There is absolutely nothing wrong with enjoying what you enjoy, or being yourself, exactly the same for feeling extrovert. There is nothing wrong here either. It's what you enjoy & who you are! Everyone is different, that's the wonder of human nature. Its labelling that is the issue.
.
The problems come when we begin to doubt who we are, & start to think it's a problem, there isn't a problem if you truly enjoy it, nothing at all, but you can help yourself to know if there is a something to address by asking yourself a few questions.
.
👉Am I hiding or running away from a feeling?
👉Do I really want to go out but I'm afraid?
👉Do I really want to be able to stay home but I'm afraid?
.
If no is the answer to all the above you are as happy as a sunflower in the sun, enjoy every moment of your happiness being you😊
.
If the answer is Yes, then you may need a little help to work on those fears, you're maybe not able to be who you are, if fear is ruling you. You can get help from a therapist, counsellor or coach who have been through the same things. So you can feel as happy as a 🌻 in the 🌞 too, you deserve too.
.
🙏BALANCE
Whether extrovert or introvert makes NO difference you can actually be both, to have a sense of wellbeing a balance is needed in your life, no fear of either, if you feel extroverted some downtime will help you feel more balanced, if you are an feel introvert some outdoor time will really help your wellbeing too. Try to make your opposite activities as fun as you can, remember to ask yourself what you would enjoy to do? Without worrying about others, life is too short to not be yourself.❤
.
Enjoy every moment. 
.
#anxiety #wellness #recovery #panic #gad #introvert #extrovert #noworries #happy #beyou

It's 𝗲𝗮𝘀𝘆 to stop yourself, your life, thinking you ARE your feelings. Anxiety👇
.
🎨@thefemalehustlers
✒@anxiety_wellbeing #coach
.
IT'S ALSO
𝗲𝗮𝘀𝘆 to just 'say' what you need to do, but 'doing' it is another thing so👇
.
I KNOW 
What the anxiety experience feels like, what a panic attack feels like, what panicking every 30 mins for months feels like, what being scared to go anywhere feels like, what fear of breathing, eating, you name it scared of the whole human experience feels like. I was focused on ANXIETY, on how I FELT, on what it COULD be? On WHEN will I panic next? On my BODY, lost in my THOUGHTS.
.
I WAS 
scared to tell
But after 6 months of running & hiding from the truth of what I was experiencing, I was so sad, exhausted, fearful, tired from it, I thought telling a doctor would never be as bad as this.
What is the worst that could happen?
Even if they told me I was mad, I could get help, I can't run from myself anymore.
.
I SPOKE
to my doc
It wasn't my worst fear
I was experiencing anxiety that had grown to a fear so BIG I was not living.
I wanted to learn about the body
Why everything had happened, happened.
About the mind
I learned there was a reason it had all began. 
Once i learned to calm my body
The mind followed.
.
THEN.
I had a thought😑
I was brilliantly FOCUSED on fear I was AMAZING at it.
Hang on could this be a strength?
My mind is incredible.
.
WHAT IF I focus on what I want?
Write, Say, Live, Sing, Draw It.
.
I'LL SEE it
I'll FEEL it
I am NOT anxiety 
It is my body's RESPONSE to overwhelm, stress, fearful thoughts.
I FOCUS on the opposite 
Wellbeing 
Learning
Growth
HUMANESS
Emotions let out
Change 
Ideas, planned & actioned. Changed my thoughts, gave me experiences that showed me what I knew from the past was not all there was to this life, don't define me. I define me.
.
I AM human
I experience human emotion
My body responds to stress with anxiety.
I am in control of my actions & how I navigate &  create my environment🤗
Focus on my GROWTH
.
YOU CAN TOO
What could you focus on?
There's a thought management download to try, click the linktree link in the bio. Helps u refocus. 
.

Which number relates? Need free help today, now? Read in 👇
.
🎨@malminder.gill.therapy 
✒@anxiety_wellbeing 
.
1. If you recognise yourself in any of this you are a normal human being.
.
2. Its OK to say its been very tough, allow yourself to get honest, let it out, crying is not weak it is energy in e-motion. It needs release.
.
3. My work is of a CBT practitioner, holistic anxiety coach. Plus I've been there. In my 20's I was panicking every 30 mins, & afraid of everything! Going out, transport, conversation, leaving my room, sleeping, eating, thinking my body etc.it was a pretty dark time not knowing anything & afraid every second of the day. So I can give you some pointers today.
.
4. Anxiety is a response, it's not the problem, yes jezzzzz it feels like it but its a response to the real problem.
.
5. When we perceive it to be the problem, we are then saying its something to fear. Fear causes anxiety & especially panic & the response is a fear based emotion. If you were in an emergency you need fear to get you out, to avoid, flight, or to defend, fight, of to freeze. You wouldn't want to stop  ask who wants a cup of tea, you're in danger! Fear is essencial, but that means that fear causes anxiety & anxiety causes fear. This is a circle we can all easily find ourselves in.
.
6. Here's how it gets worse without you even knowing how it did, after all you are doing what you believe to be the right thing.
.
Example 
💭I feel anxious, this is not good, its the problem so I am going to Avoid what I think is the danger, anxiety. 
.
👍If you do avoid(flight)this is a signal to the mind, whose job it is to keep you alive📨
.
📨🧠We are trying to avoid what we think is the danger, anxiety. So it must be the danger, next time avoid again, thats how we survive. 
.
Its doing a great job, remember your mind cannot tell of you are afraid & ran because you saw a snake or if you are afraid of.
Anxiety 
Going out 
People 
Etc. 
.
7. Its normal to feel afraid when anxious, & normal to become afraid of what happend there. The best thing you can do is never avoid anxiety, stay & ask for advice, guidance, tools, they are out there❤
.
#anxiety #anxietycoach

I saw this and thought we all needed a reminder to check up on others, to try not to judge that a behaviour was something bad.👇
.
Chadwick Boseman 1976-2020 : actor : played the black panther ❤ sadly passed away last year after a battle with cancer.
 📽@ stan hiddle tik tok
.
Example, if you didn't know that he was battling cancer what might you assume from his behaviour?
.
He's lazy 
Must have gone out last night 
He's not serious about this commitment 
Etc 
And you'd be wrong.
.
Then with this negative perception that is not true, what would you feel? Angry?
🤬Here i am trying hard & he doesn't care!
Then what might you do?
Ignore him? Be funny, off with him?
Etc 
What would be the consequences?
.
Take this reminder today & try not to judge others, because you don't know anything, so first try compassion, we are all human you'll need that compassion 1 day too.
.
Give anger you'll get defense back 
Give compassion you'll get a human ❤
_______________
.
I am sad that he passed away. His character in the film Black panther was something we had needed for years & was looking forward to seeing more.
.
Watch the film because you could have a negative perception of black people that had been fed to you, & if you do, this will effect how you think, feel & act. How would that effect your behaviour? What would be the consequences?
.
Imagine if someone had already a negative perception of you, how might you react to that? 

Negative? 
Angry?
Defensive?
.
Then what would that cause? 
.
Always in whatever situation you are in check your perspective. Is it true? Question it.
Break the circle. 
.
